            <div type="general">
               <p xml:space="preserve">Meloussi is a village in the Central Tunisian Sidi Bouzid Governorate, located in a rather isolated area, over 20 km far from the nearest highway, namely the one connecting <ref type="profile" target="profile_{Sidi Bouzid}_0">Sidi Bouzid</ref> and <ref type="profile" target="profile_{Meknassi}_01">Meknassi</ref>.</p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">The population of Meloussi belongs to the Rdadya or Ouled Raddad (Rdādya or Ūlǟd Raddǟd) tribal group, which is a part of the Ouled Aziz (Ūlǟd ʕZīz) tribe, which in turn belongs to the Hamǟmma tribal confederation. </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">The inhabitants of Meloussi suffer from poor power supply and infrastructure in their area.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p xml:space="preserve">To the best of our knowledge hitherto no research has been done on the dialect of Meloussi, however this dialect is linguistically investigated within the TUNOCENT project.</p>
            </div>
